weet, we only choose one variable from each of them: select full_name from place, full_text from extended_tweet. If the tweet is longer than 140 characters, the tweet would be truncated to put into the text variable, and the original tweet would be put into the full_text variable. We add a new variable called original_text to restore the tweet and make constructing analysis more convenient. 3.2 extract words Next, we need to tokenize the word to make analysis related to property of words in each tweet.For this task, we use the tokenize_tweets() function from the tokenizers library, since there are some special characters like hashtag and usernames that might otherwise be stripped away using other tokenizer. Below is an example for how it tokenizes one of the tweets. ## [1] &quot;@cryptocevo Why #KISHU ?
